                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1ra">Fols. 1ra-4</locus>vb; 145va-146vb: Theological treatise composed of the quotations from the Church Fathers, unidentified.<q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 1ra-4vb: እምቃለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቄርሎስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘለእስክንድርያ፡ ውእቱ፡ እምኈልቆሙ፡ ለአበው፡ ሊቃነ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ፳ወ፬፡ በሣልስ፡ እምድርሳናቲሁ።...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written possibly in the main hand or in a similar hand. The text continues from 4vb onto fol. 145va, after the Gospel of Mark (this is also indicated by the note ሀሎ፡ በፍጻሜ፡ ማርቆስ, in the bottom margin fol. rv). It includes quotations from St. Cyril of Alexandria, John Chrysostom, Hippolytus, Heraclius, Theodotos, Gregory of Nazianzos, Severos, John of Alexandria, Cyriacus, Theodosius, Basil, John of Antiochia, Sanutius, Zakariah Yahya, Philotheus, Athanasius, Ignatios, Innocentius, John of Jerusalem, Epiphanius of Cyprus. The quotations mostly corresponds to the text of Haymanotä ʾabäw, cp. the  EOTC, Addis Abäba 1967 A.M. (and usually follow one another, e.g.:
fol. 2rab (አቡሊድስ), fol. 2ra lines 3-5 correspond to Haymanotä ʾabäw 132, verse 2, line 1;
fol. 2ra lines 5-9 correspond to 132, verse 3, line 1 - verse 4, line 1;
fol. 2ra lines 9-10 correspond to 132, verse 5, line 1;
fol. 2ra lines 11-12 correspond to 133, verse 11;
fol. 2ra lines 12-19 correspond to 134, verse 19, line 3 - verse 20 to the end;
fol. 2ra lines 20-23 correspond to 136, verses 36, lines 1-3;
fol. 2ra line 23 - 2rb line 8 correspond to 136, verse 37, line 3 (with one change - በመለኮት instead of በሥጋ) - verse 38, line 2;
fol. 4vb, lines 13-21 (አግናጥዮስ);  
lines 16-17 correspond to 36, verse 3, line 1;
lines 17-21 correspond to 37, verse 4, line 1-4;
fol. 145vb, lines 1-6 (አቡሊድስ) and lines 2-6 correspond to 142, verses 5-6.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#104ra">Fols. 104ra</locus>-vb, 102rb, ls.13-20: Theological discourse on the Trinity, unidentified.<q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 104ra-vb: እጽሕፍ፡ ተዋህዶተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ እምቅድመ፡ ይትፈጠሩ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወምድር፡ ወኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡ ነበሩ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ በሠለስቱ፡ አካላት፡ ወበአሐዱ፡ መለኮት፡ አብሰ፡ ውእቱ፡ የአምር፡ እምኀበ፡ ዘወፅአ፡...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#234vb">Fol. 234vb</locus>: Ownership note, rhymed.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 234vb: ዝመጽሐፍ፨ ዘወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፨ ዘተሣየጠ፡ በንዋዩ፨ ሶበ፡ ሀለየ፡ ፍቅረ፡ ክርስቶስ፨ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ከመ፡ ይትዋረሥ፡ ዘይኩን፡ ሎቱ፡ ለሕይወተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፨ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘተአገሎ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ይኩን፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳው{ሎስ}፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 234vb:This (is) the book of Wäldä Giyorgis, Who acquired (it) with his own money  when he was pondering about the love of Christ, To inherit the Kingdom of Heaven, That it might be for him for the life of (his) body and soul. He who stole it or took it away shall be excommunicated by the word of Peter and Paul.</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#282ra">Fols. 282ra-283</locus>vb: Theological treatise on heresies, unidentified, incomplete.<q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 282ra-283vb: ንንግርኬ፡ ዘለፋሆሙ፡ ለረሲዓን፡ ስብልያኖስ፡ ይቤ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ፩ገጽ፡ ንሕነሰ፡ ንብል፡ ፫ገጽ፡ ፩ራእይ፡ ፫አካል፡ ፩አምላክ ። ፫አስማት፡ ፩እግዚአብሔር።... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#00"/>
                           <desc>Fols. 284ra-vb, 281va-vb: Treatise on the genealogy of Christ, unidentified.  </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 284ra-vb: ዳዊት፡ ቢወልድ፡ ናታንን፡ ሰሎሞንን፡ ናታን፡ ቢወልድ፡ ሚልኩ፡ ሹሻንን፡ አግብቶ፡ ኔሪን፡ ወልዶ፡ ሞተ፡ ሹሻንን፡ ኔሪን፡ ሕዝላ፡ ከኢዮአቄም፡ ገብታ፡...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. The text continues from fol. 284vb onto 281va. It is a (unknown?) treatise on the genealogy of Christ, harmonizing the genealogies from Mt. 1:1-17 and Lk. 3:23-38, with passages based on the Old Testament history (from Rahab and Salmon to Azariah).
                        </item>
